Many of these factors are concentrated among older adults, but younger people with certain underlying health problems are also at risk.
In older adults, the number of white blood cells that find and help eliminate infections can decline.
On the other hand, itâ€™s still only a minority of older adults who are facing the most severe consequences of Covid-19.
Older adults may face the greatest risks, but the Covid-19 outbreak affects everyoneWhile the majority of the people infected by Covid-19 will survive, there will be significant ripple effects if large numbers of older adults get very ill or die from the disease.
So the measures we use to protect older adults, both physically and mentally, can help younger people in similar situations.